WEBVTT

00:00:01.679 --> 00:00:04.119
Above the old fish market, a glassblower

00:00:04.239 --> 00:00:06.239
bends neon the way her father taught

00:00:06.299 --> 00:00:08.879
her, over an open flame, one letter

00:00:08.919 --> 00:00:09.519
at a time.

00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:12.819
This city once glowed with 400 hand-bent

00:00:12.919 --> 00:00:13.379
signs.

00:00:13.719 --> 00:00:15.439
Fewer than 60 are left.

00:00:15.919 --> 00:00:18.079
When a storefront goes dark, the owners

00:00:18.159 --> 00:00:20.219
climb her stairs and ask for light.

00:00:20.520 --> 00:00:22.539
"A sign is a promise," she says.

00:00:22.819 --> 00:00:24.459
It tells the street that somebody is

00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:25.139
still home.

00:00:27.399 --> 00:00:29.499
Sobre el viejo mercado de pescado, una

00:00:29.599 --> 00:00:31.719
vidriera dobla el neón como le enseñó

00:00:31.799 --> 00:00:34.359
su padre sobre una llama abierta, una

00:00:34.439 --> 00:00:35.439
letra a la vez.

00:00:35.519 --> 00:00:38.279
Esta ciudad alguna vez brilló con cuatrocientos

00:00:38.359 --> 00:00:39.839
letreros doblados a mano.

00:00:39.999 --> 00:00:41.219
Quedan menos de sesenta.
